ssh-audit (SSH security configuration auditing tool)

ssh-audit is a tool for SSH server and client configuration auditing.
Key features:
- SSH1 and SSH2 protocol server support
- Analyze SSH version compatibility based on algorithm information
- Audit key exchange, host key, encryption and message authentication
  algorithms, and output info (available since, removed/disabled,
  unsafe/weak/legacy)
- Provide recommendations for hardening configuration
Homepage: https://github.com/jtesta/ssh-audit
